## Key Equations/Formulas

```
One-Way ANOVA Table:
  Source     | SS     | df     | MS           | F
  Factor     | SS_A   | a-1    | SS_A/(a-1)   | MS_A / MS_E
  Error      | SS_E   | N-a    | SS_E/(N-a)   |
  Total      | SS_T   | N-1    |              |

Eta squared:
  η² = SS_factor / SS_total

Grubbs test: tests the most extreme value for being a significant outlier
  H₀: no outlier in the data
  H₁: the most extreme value is an outlier
```

